node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021 tagging @dlcanxiety, @fightthroughmentalhealth, and @notsosecretdiaryofanxiety. May be an image of text that says 'Things People With Anxiety May Do That Čan Come Across As "Rude": @FIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo shared by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021 tagging @dlcanxiety, @fightthroughmentalhealth, and @notsosecretdiaryofanxiety. May be an image of text that says 'Things People With Anxiety May Do That Čan Come Across As "Rude": @FIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Cancel plans They tend to either have an excuse, agree to the plan and cancel last minute, or just not show up. It is most likely that they have experienced severe anxiety that causes them to cancel plans that they were initially interested in. @FIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Not responding to calls/ texts Their anxiety holds them back from responding to text messages or returning phone calls. Ifthey engage in such, they will experience the dreadful symptoms of anxiety, which would much rather be avoided. @FIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says '•Lack of eye contact When anxiety becomes overbearing, it can be difficult to maintain eye contact- whether it be while speaking or listening during a conversation. Some people avoid social interaction all together. Others prefer not having the spotlight on them when being spoken to. @EIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Distancing from others People with anxiety sometimes distance themselves from people because they want to "focus on themself." They don't want to waste their time and energy if they are not in their ideal state, because then it just won't be fun for them to be around, so they distance themself. @FIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Asking you to repeał things Sometimes people with anxiety may have their mind in a different place and can be overwhelmed with thoughts, otherwise known as brain fog' Sometimes it can be hard to process information, and they don't purposely do it. @FIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Getting agitated Sometimes, they get snappy with people, have an abrupt or harsh tone, or blow up over something that seems small, without even meaning to. Anxiety just makes people so on edge that, sometimes, the slightest thing can push them over. @FIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Not engaging in conversation Sometimes people with anxiety can find conversation awkward or hard to maintain, especially when in a groop of people. They don't mean it in a rude way, anxiety can manifest itself in many different ways. @FIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Talking too much/ interrupting Ocasionally someone may get so anxious when they are out with friends and there is an awkward silence or no one is talking. So they then feel the need to talk more. @FIGHTTHROUGHMENTALHEALTH'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says '#2 Mindfulness Research shows that mindfulness is particularly effective combatting depression and anxiety. Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says '#3 Take your vitamins Your brain needs a lot of fuel to power all its complex processes. In fact, it has some of the highest energy requirements amongst all of your body organs. Vitamins, minerals & other nutrients in your diet have a direct impact on your brain's functions, including memory, learning, concentration & emotional regulation. @yourheights The braincare company'.

Photo by DLC Anxiety Worldwide 🌍 on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says '#4 Play brain games Brain activities that encourage you to think hard, and explore a situation critically, enhance your cognitive capacity and strengthen your brain's resilience to stressful situations that may sabotage your mental health. @yourheights The braincare company'.
